The '''Schools Consent Project''' is a charity organisation based in the [[United Kingdom|UK]] which delivers sexual education workshops focusing on the topic of [[sexual consent|consent]].<ref name="Sexrobots">{{cite web |language=Dutch |accessdate=16 September 2017 |first=Kate |title=SEKSROBOTS De seksrobot die je zo kunt instellen dat ze tegenstribbe lt is echt niet oké |work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |last=Parker |year=2017 |url=https://www.vice.com/be/article/vbb9a4/de-seksrobot-die-je-zo-kunt-instellen-dat-ze-tegenstribbelt-is-echt-niet-oke |trans-title=SEX ROBOTS The sex robot that you can set up to counterbalance is really not okay}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Rebecca |last=Wright |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915225315/https://rightsinfo.org/where-does-the-new-justice-secretary-stand-on-human-rights/ |url=https://rightsinfo.org/where-does-the-new-justice-secretary-stand-on-human-rights/ |accessdate=16 September 2017 |date=15 June 2017 |title=Where does the new justice secretary stand on human-rights |archivedate=15 September 2017 |website=RightsInfo.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915224419/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/nathalie-greenfield/sex-education_b_12756038.html |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/nathalie-greenfield/sex-education_b_12756038.html |title=Why Sex Ed Really Is Power |date=2 November 2016 |last=Greenfield |archivedate=15 September 2017 |deadurl=no |first=Nathalie |work=[[Huffington Post]] The Blog |accessdate=16 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915223144/https://www.ayoungertheatre.com/author/ettie/ |deadurl=no |url=https://www.ayoungertheatre.com/author/ettie/ |title=Ettie Bailey-King |archivedate=15 September 2017 |website=AYoungerTheatre.com |accessdate=16 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Hey, Lawyers – Leave Them Kids Alone |first=Luk |work=[[Spiked (magazine)|Spike]] |last=Gittos |archiveurl=https://web